olive oil
1 cucumber
1 radish
1 packet Crumbed Chicken Breast Strips
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Corn Chips
1 packet sour cream
1 bag coriander
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend

• Chop cucumber and radish

• Heat frying pan over medium-high
heat with enough olive oil to coat
base of pan. Cook chicken until
golden and cooked through,
3-4 mins each side
• In the last minute of cooking time,
add spice blend, turning chicken to
coat

• In a large bowl, combine cabbage
mix, cucumber, radish, chipotle
sauce, mayonnaise and a drizzle of
olive oil. Season
• Lightly crush corn chips
• Plate up slaw and top with chicken,
crushed corn chips, cheese and sour
cream.
• Tear over coriander to serve